  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0d82\u0dc4\u0dbd \u0d9c\u0db8\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0d9a\u0dca \u0da2\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Many Bulathsinhala villages will be submerged",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the irrigation engineers, two sluice gates of the Kukulegaga Reservoir have been opened due to the heavy rainfall, and a water capacity of about 200 cubic meters per tappere is being released into the small river.",
        "Due to this, many low lands and several roads in Bulathsinhala area have been flooded, according to Mr. Prasad Perera, Divisional Secretary of Bulathsinhala.",
        "As of now, several areas including the Paragoda Atambagas junction on the Bulathsinghala Molkawa main road have been flooded, traffic has come to a standstill and the people are facing severe difficulties.",
        "Even now, there is heavy rain in those areas and people are seen using their fingers to travel."
      ],
